Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:26.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs100\t(,\fs110)\frz1\fad(3000,500)\fsp0\fscx120\pos(960,800)\b0\shad0\bord0}地          球          脉          动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.90,0:00:40.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,100年前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A hundred years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.66,0:00:44.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上生活着15亿人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}there were one and a half billion people on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.46,0:00:51.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今 已有超过60亿人拥挤在 我们这颗脆弱的星球上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, over six billion crowd our fragile planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.74,0:00:58.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管如此 地球上仍有一些 人类极少涉足的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But even so, there are still places barely touched by humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.30,0:01:07.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这部专题片将把你带到最后的蛮荒之地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This series will take to the last wildernesses
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.46,0:01:12.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,展示这个星球的风貌 和你以前从未见过的野生动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and show you the planet and its wildlife as you have never seen them before.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.70,0:01:51.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs120\fsp17.5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1240)\b1\shad0\bord0}两        极        之        间
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.15,0:02:00.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1080)\bord0\shad3}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.86,0:02:05.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一下一个没有太阳的世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Imagine our world without sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.66,0:02:12.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄帝企鹅正在挑战地球上最严酷的环境\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Male Emperor Penguins are facing the nearest that exists on planet Earth -
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.26,0:02:14.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极洲的冬天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}winter in Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.46,0:02:18.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑夜漫无休止\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's continuously dark
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.30,0:02:22.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,气温下降到零下70℃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and temperatures drop to minus seventy degrees centigrade.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.34,0:02:36.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其它动物早已逃离 只有企鹅留了下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The penguins stay when all other creatures have fled
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.70,0:02:39.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为每只企鹅都护卫着一件宝贝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}because each guards a treasure:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.38,0:02:42.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗躺在它们脚背上的蛋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a single egg rested on the top of its feet
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.22,0:02:46.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,依靠耷拉下来的肚皮上的绒毛保持温暖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and kept warm beneath the downy bulge of its stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.10,0:02:53.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们没有食物 也没有水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is no food and no water for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:57.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且整整4个月见不到太阳\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they will not see the sun again for four months.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.30,0:03:01.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这绝对是动物们经受过的最严酷的考验\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Surely no greater ordeal is faced by any animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.82,0:03:14.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳已远离南极\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the sun departs from the Antarctic
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.94,0:03:18.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,照耀在遥远的北方天空\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it lightens the skies in the far north.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.86,0:03:28.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在是三月\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's March
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.26,0:03:31.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阳光重返北极腹地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and light returns to the high Arctic,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.26,0:03:34.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,驱走了4个月的黑暗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}sweeping away four months of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.30,0:03:49.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一只北极熊苏醒了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A polar bear stirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.98,0:03:53.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个冬天 它都在洞穴里度过\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She has been in her den the whole winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.38,0:03:57.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的出现标志着春天的到来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her emergence marks the beginning of spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.98,0:04:02.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长达数月的地下闭居已经结束\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After months of confinement underground
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.58,0:04:04.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它从斜坡上一滑而下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}she toboggans down the slope.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.74,0:04:06.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许是为了清洁皮毛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Perhaps to clean her fur,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.98,0:04:10.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许只是因为高兴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}perhaps for sheer joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.30,0:04:29.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的幼熊们第一次注视着 这个明亮的新世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Her cubs gaze out of their bright new world for the very first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.22,0:04:33.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母熊召唤着熊崽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The female calls them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.94,0:04:39.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但在这个陡峭的斜坡上 踏出第一步可不太容易\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but this steep slope is not the easiest place to take your first steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.46,0:04:54.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是它们太饿了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But they are hungry
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.10,0:04:55.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,急切盼着来到母亲身旁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and eager to reach their mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:04:59.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个特别的日子里  母熊已经推迟了喂奶的时间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}who's delayed feeding them on this special day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.46,0:05:01.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在该是履行承诺的时候了  乳汁是巨大的诱惑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now she lures them with the promise of milk,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.98,0:05:09.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自从熊崽们两个多月前又聋又瞎地 在雪下出生以来 母乳就是它们唯一的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the only food the cubs have known since they were born deaf and blind beneath the snow some two months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.74,0:05:28.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的母亲已有5个月没有进食了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their mother has not eaten for five months
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.98,0:05:31.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,失去了一半的体重\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and has lost half her body weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:37.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在它将仅剩的一点脂肪 变成乳汁喂养它的宝贝们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now she converts the last of her fat reserves into milk for her cubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.98,0:05:58.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,春天的太阳带来了温暖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The spring sun brings warmth
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:01.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但对母熊而言却是一个问题\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but also a problem for the mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.78,0:06:04.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海面的冰层开始融化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It starts to melt the sea ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.90,0:06:08.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而母熊则需要在那里捕杀海豹 喂养幼熊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}That is where she hunts for the seal she needs to feed her cubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.02,0:06:12.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此它必须在冰层破碎之前到达那里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And she must get there before the ice breaks up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.26,0:06:19.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而现在的气温仍然有-30℃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For now though it's still minus thirty degrees
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.46,0:06:22.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,熊崽们必须回到洞中避寒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the cubs must have the shelter of the den.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.18,0:06:39.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在是北极熊现身后的第6天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's six days since the bears emerged
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.34,0:06:42.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,春色匆匆\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and spring is advancing rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.06,0:06:46.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但即使是现在 暴风雪 仍会在毫无征兆的情况下来袭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But even now blizzards can strike without warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.78,0:06:54.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幼小的熊崽很容易冻僵  躲在洞穴中可能会更舒服些\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Being so small, the cubs are easily chilled and they will be more comfortable resting in the den.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.78,0:06:58.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是母熊必须得把它们带到外边活动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But their mother must keep them out and active.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.26,0:07:00.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,饥饿将它折磨得虚弱不堪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She's becoming weak from hunger
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.98,0:07:04.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而这片产仔的斜坡上没有一点食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and there's no food on these nursery slopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.42,0:07:12.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海面上的冰层依然坚固\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sea ice still holds firm,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.86,0:07:15.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这种情况不会持续太久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it won't last much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.54,0:07:19.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第10天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Day 10,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.62,0:07:23.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母熊已经带领幼熊离巢1英里远\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the mother has led her cubs a mile from the den.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.18,0:07:26.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在该是考验它们的时候了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's time to put them to the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.38,0:07:31.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的信心日益膨胀\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They've grown enormously in confidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.22,0:07:34.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过它们并不像母熊那样着急\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they don't have their mother's sense of urgency.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.90,0:07:53.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后 它们似乎做好了旅行的准备\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At last it seems that they're ready for their journey
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.38,0:07:55.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们刚好赶得及\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they're only just in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.30,0:07:59.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离岸几英里远的海面上  冰层已经开始崩裂\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for a few miles from the coast the ice is already splitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.86,0:08:09.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在母熊将猎杀海豹  获取紧需的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now the mother can start hunting for the seals they must have,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.54,0:08:13.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而它也正带着熊崽们 进入一个危险的新世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but she's leading her cubs into a dangerous new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.66,0:08:20.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约有近一半的幼熊 会在第一年的冰上历险中丧生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nearly half of all cubs die in their first year out on the ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.50,0:08:32.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夏季意味着全天24小时的日照\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Summer brings 24 hours of sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.94,0:08:36.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,融化的冰雪不断改变着地貌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the thawing shifting landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.94,0:08:44.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在更远的北极苔原上  冬雪几乎已经完全消失\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Further south the winter snows have almost cleared from the Arctic tundra.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.94,0:08:55.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是加拿大北部荒野\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Northern Canada's wild frontier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:59.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大自然正在此上演着一幕最壮观的演出\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here nature stages one of her greatest dramas -
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.90,0:09:13.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每年 300万迁徙的北美驯鹿 都将穿越北极苔原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every year three million caribou migrate across the Arctic tundra.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.54,0:09:30.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,庞大的鹿群只有在空中 才能完全领略它的壮观\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The immensity of the herd can only be properly appreciated from the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.66,0:09:44.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有的鹿群一年得走上2000多英里  才能到达新鲜草场\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some herds travel over 2,000 miles a year in search of fresh pastures.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.46,0:09:50.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是动物界中最长的陆地迁徙\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the longest overland migration made by any animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.18,0:10:03.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们总是不停地赶路\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're constantly on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.50,0:10:07.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新生的小鹿必须 在出生的第一天就站起来奔跑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Newborn calves have to be up and running the day they are born.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.70,0:10:31.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是庞大的鹿群并非独自旅行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the vast herds do not travel alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.74,0:10:36.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Wolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.26,0:10:42.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,8～10只狼组成的小股部队 悄悄地尾随着迁徙的大军\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Packs of them, eight to ten strong, shadow the migration.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.82,0:10:46.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们已是饥肠辘辘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they are hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.66,0:10:55.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的目标就是新生的小鹿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's the newly born calves that they are after.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.46,0:11:07.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直冲向鹿群是一种制造恐慌的战术\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Running directly at the herd is a ploy to generate panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.34,0:11:18.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鹿群奔散开来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The herd breaks up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.66,0:11:22.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狼群便更容易锁定单个目标\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and now it's easier to target an individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.66,0:11:36.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,混乱中一只小鹿与它的母亲失散了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the chaos a calf is separated from its mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.98,0:11:44.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小鹿虽然很小\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The calf is young,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.46,0:11:49.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但如果全速奔跑起来  它仍可以比狼跑得更快\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it can outrun the wolf if only it manages to keep its footing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.10,0:12:04.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种情况下一般有两种可能\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At this stage the odds are even -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.02,0:12:06.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一是驯鹿自己犯下错误\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}either the caribou will make a mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.22,0:12:09.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,否则就是狼追出1英里之后选择放弃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}or after a mile the wolf will give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.66,0:12:58.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在是苔原的仲夏时节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Midsummer on the tundra
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.78,0:13:01.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会出现日落\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the sun does not set.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.22,0:13:07.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个高纬度地区  太阳辐射只能斜射到这片土地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At these latitudes the sun's rays are glancing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.86,0:13:13.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到达地面的能量很少  并不足以支持树木生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and not enough of their energy reaches the ground to enable trees to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:20.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由此往南500英里的地方 才有可能生长着树木\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}You'll need to travel 500 miles south from here before that is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.62,0:13:30.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些矮小的灌木标志着森林界线\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These stunted shrubs mark the tree line -
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.10,0:13:33.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北方森林由此开始\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the beginning of the boreal forest -
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.46,0:13:35.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是泰加林带\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the taiga.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.66,0:13:47.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,针叶树的针状树叶根本不能食用\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The needle-shaped leaves of the conifers are virtually inedible
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.66,0:13:51.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以生活在这片森林里的动物非常稀少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so this forest supports very little animal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.78,0:13:59.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是个寂静的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a silent place
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:03.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪地上没有被踩过的脚印\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}where the snow is unmarked by footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.10,0:14:13.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每到北极冬季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the Arctic winter
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.94,0:14:18.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪便为这片土地盖上一层广袤无边的银毯\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}snow forms a continuous blanket across the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.22,0:14:21.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是随着春天渐渐从南方赶来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But as spring creeps up from the south
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.14,0:14:24.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,泰加林带也揭开了它的面纱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the taiga is unveiled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.22,0:14:32.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这片环绕着地球的广大森林\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This vast forest circling the globe
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:35.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,容纳了地球上1/3的树木\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}contains a third of all the trees on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.62,0:14:37.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生了大量氧气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and produces so much oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.82,0:14:41.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而改变了大气成分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it changes the composition of the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.98,0:14:45.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着我们向南行进\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As we travel south
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.82,0:14:48.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的影响力逐渐增强\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so the sun's influence grows stronger
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.82,0:14:54.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北纬50°的地方是一场重大变革的起点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and at 50 degrees of latitude a radical transformation begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.34,0:15:10.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于有足够长的夏季  阔叶林得以取代针叶林\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Summers here are long enough for broadleaf trees to replace conifers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.78,0:15:14.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阔叶树的树叶更容易食用和消化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Broadleaves are much easier to eat and digest
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:19.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此动物们也能获得 太阳馈赠给它们的那部分能量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so now animals can collect their share of the energy that has come from the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.18,0:15:22.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在是夏天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's summer
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.14,0:15:25.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,森林中一片生机勃勃的景象\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and these forests are bustling with life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.90,0:15:53.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是好景不长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the good times will not last.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.86,0:16:00.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于严寒的原因 阔叶树得在冬天落叶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Broad leaves must be shed in winter for their damage by frost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.30,0:16:01.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,树叶消失之后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As they disappear,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.82,0:16:06.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大地一片荒凉 动物们的食物日益稀少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so the land becomes barren with little for animals to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.50,0:16:16.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,居民们只得迁往他处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The inhabitants must migrate,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.02,0:16:18.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者冬眠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}hibernate,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.30,0:16:21.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者忍受几个月的饥荒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}or face months of near starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.14,0:16:40.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是远东豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Amur leopard -
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.98,0:16:43.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,世界上最稀有的猫科动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the rarest cat in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.86,0:16:49.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是俄罗斯东部的落叶林\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, in the deciduous forests of eastern Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.98,0:16:52.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冬天使得狩猎变得相当困难\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the winter makes hunting very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.74,0:16:54.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,猎物非常稀少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Pray animals are scarce,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.46,0:16:56.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也没有可以隐蔽的植被\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and there's no concealing vegetation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.22,0:17:04.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小豹已有一岁大了 仍旧依靠着它的母亲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The cub is a year old and still dependent on its mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.34,0:17:15.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鹿经常会死于严酷的冬天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Deer are frequent casualties of the harsh winter
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.82,0:17:19.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些豹子不会介意吃死鹿的肉充饥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and these leopards are not above scavenging from a corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.26,0:17:23.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非洲豹根本不能在这里生存\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}African leopards could never survive here,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.74,0:17:28.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而俄罗斯的猫科动物则有厚实的皮毛 帮助它们抵挡严寒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the Russian cats have thick fur to shield them from the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.38,0:17:38.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今世界上只存活着40只远东豹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are only forty Amur leopards left in the wild
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.18,0:17:40.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且这个数目还在减少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and that number is falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.62,0:17:43.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与许多动物一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Like so many creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.06,0:17:49.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于盗猎和栖息地遭到破坏  这些大猫已经被推到了灭绝的边缘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the cats have been pushed to the very edge of extinction by hunting and the destruction of their habitat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.66,0:17:57.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远东豹充分暴露了自然遗产的脆弱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Amur leopard symbolises the fragility of our natural heritage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.70,0:18:05.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个物种的未来寄托在 为数不多的几只母豹身上 就好比这一只\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The future of an entire species hangs on survival of a tiny number of mothers like this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.22,0:18:13.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有动物 无论稀有的还是常见的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All animals, rare or common,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.62,0:18:17.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,归根结底都依赖于太阳的能量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}ultimately depend for their energy on the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.90,0:18:27.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在日本 每到樱花盛开的时节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In Japan the arrival of the cherry blossom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.62,0:18:30.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也意味着春天的来临\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}announces the beginning of spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:55.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳用能量创作了一幅色彩艳丽的山水画\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sun's energy brings colour to the landscape.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.94,0:19:08.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球每年绕着太阳公转\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The earth, as it makes its annual journey around the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.54,0:19:10.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时也绕着一根倾斜的轴自转\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}spins on a tilted axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.98,0:19:15.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正是这种倾斜造成了季节变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And it's this tilt that creates the seasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.50,0:19:43.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,世间万物随着季节的变迁不断改变\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The advance of the seasons brings constant change.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.82,0:19:47.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在北方 随着太阳影响力的减弱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the sun's influence diminishes in the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.82,0:19:52.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美洲落叶林开始放慢生命的脚步\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so the deciduous forests of America begin to shut down
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.34,0:19:57.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们落下树叶 以应对 即将到来的几个月的严寒和黑暗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}losing their leaves in preparation for the dark cold months ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.22,0:20:14.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个季节接替另一个季节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One season hands over to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.14,0:20:16.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有的生物在腐败中获得兴盛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some organisms thrive on decay,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.94,0:20:23.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而更多的却得专门为冬天做好准备  以度过缺少阳光的日子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but most must make special preparations for winter and a life with little sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.50,0:20:45.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,动物们成群结队踏上 寻找食物和温暖的长途旅程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Whole populations of animals are now forced to travel great distances in pursuit of food and warmth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.78,0:21:00.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,30万只花脸鸭集体迁往南方的韩国  躲避西伯利亚的严冬\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}300,000 Baikal teal gather to escape from the Siberian winter by migrating south to Korea -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.82,0:21:07.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仅这一群便集中了世界上所有的花脸鸭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the world's entire population in a single flock.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.18,0:21:15.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是 世界上有些地方却没有四季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But there are parts of the world that have no seasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.78,0:21:22.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在热带地区 太阳辐射直射大地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the tropics the sun's rays strike the earth head on
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.82,0:21:26.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,全年始终或多或少地 受到这种影响力的控制\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and their strength is more or less constant all year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.58,0:21:32.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此 这里的丛林茂密葱郁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}That is why the jungle grows so vigourously
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.42,0:21:35.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生命在此欣欣向荣\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and supports so much life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.58,0:21:40.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些森林仅覆盖了地球表面的3%\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This forest covers only 3 percent of the planet's surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.34,0:21:45.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但其中的动植物种类却占到了全球的50%\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it contains more than 50 percent of all its plants and animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.98,0:21:52.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,树冠层是生命最繁荣的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The canopy is particularly rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.22,0:21:54.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里有猴子、鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are monkeys, birds
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.26,0:21:56.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有数百万种昆虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and millions of species of insects,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.50,0:21:59.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至于确切数量我们不得而知\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}exactly how many we have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.74,0:22:05.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从上到下 森林的特点也在发生改变\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The character of the forest changes as we descend,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.14,0:22:07.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,越往下就越阴暗潮湿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}becoming ever darker and damper,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.70,0:22:11.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,适合各种不同种类的动植物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}favouring different kinds of animals and plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.10,0:22:20.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有不到2%的阳光能够到达丛林地表\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Less than 2 percent of the sunlight reaches the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.38,0:22:24.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即便如此 这里的生物种类也异常丰富\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but even here there is extraordinary variety.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.82,0:22:38.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在新几内亚岛上生活着42种不同的极乐鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the great island of New Guinea there are 42 different species of birds of paradise,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.34,0:22:40.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种比一种奇异\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}each more bizarre than the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.86,0:23:08.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这片森林异常富饶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This forest is so rich
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.70,0:23:12.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,营养美味的食物唾手可得\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that nourishing food can be gathered very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.06,0:23:17.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这也使得雄六羽极乐鸟 有时间去关心其它的事\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}That leaves the male six-plumed bird of paradise with time to concentrate on other matters
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.78,0:23:20.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如打扫它的「舞台」\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}like tidying up his display area.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.22,0:23:32.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整块地方必须干净整洁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Everything must be spick and span.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.94,0:23:42.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,万事具备\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.94,0:24:04.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常精彩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Very impressive,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.50,0:24:06.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可惜没有观众\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but no one is watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.42,0:24:12.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,华丽极乐鸟利用鸣叫吸引异性\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The superb bird of paradise calls to attract a female.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.26,0:24:17.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它似乎更为走运\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And he has more luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.50,0:24:22.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么 接下来它该怎么做 才能获得芳心呢？\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But what does he have to do to really impress her?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.46,0:24:50.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雌鸟退后考虑一番 准备作出决定\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She retires to consider her verdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.86,0:24:59.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄鸟不免有些沮丧\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's hard not to feel deflated
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.30,0:25:02.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它已经倾尽全力 却还是没有合格\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}when even your best isn't good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.90,0:25:27.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除了陆地之外 太阳也同样 影响着海洋中的生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sun influences life in the oceans just as it does on land.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.62,0:26:18.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当海浪和洋流把大量营养物质翻上 沐浴着阳光的表层海水时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Its richest parts are those where waves and currents bring fertilising nutrients
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.00,0:26:21.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里便成了最热闹的用餐场所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to surface waters that are bathed in sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.62,0:26:26.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南非好望角外的海域就有这种神奇的魔力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The seas off the Cape in South Africa have this magic recipe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.02,0:26:28.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且产量还非常高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and are hugely productive.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.02,0:26:34.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夏季是丰产季节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Summer is the time of plenty
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.14,0:26:37.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也是海豹的繁殖季节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and it's now that the seals start to breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.42,0:27:06.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大白鲨的突袭仅持续短短一秒左右\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The strike of a great white shark lasts a mere second.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.10,0:27:13.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,放慢40倍的画面为你呈现了 这个巨型掠食者的纯熟技巧与强悍力量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Slowing it down forty times reveals the technique and immense strength of this massive predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.38,0:27:52.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦突袭失败\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If surprise fails,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.50,0:27:54.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲨鱼就会展开追击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}there will be a chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.26,0:28:07.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲨鱼的直线速度更快\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The shark is faster on a straight course
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.46,0:28:10.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是转向却不如海豹灵活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it can't turn as sharply as the seal,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.02,0:28:15.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是敏捷与力量的对抗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}its agility versus power.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.22,0:29:11.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等到海豹结束繁殖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once the seals have finished breeding
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.58,0:29:14.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大白鲨便会继续前进\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the giant sharks will move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.42,0:29:22.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以肯定的是  大白鲨长途跋涉数千英里横越大洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's now becoming clear that great whites migrate thousands of miles across the oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.06,0:29:26.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是为了在不同海域 享用这种季节性的盛宴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to harvest seasonal abundances in different seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.18,0:29:55.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳烘晒着热带地区的海水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sun, beating down on tropical waters,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.54,0:29:58.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,驱动了全球天气系统\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}powers the weather systems of the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.62,0:30:01.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海水受热蒸发成水蒸气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Moisture evaporates from the warming ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.46,0:30:04.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上升并形成巨大的风暴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and rises to create great storms.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.78,0:30:27.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风在外海形成\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The winds generated out at sea
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.46,0:30:30.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,侵入大陆席卷内陆地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}sweep inland across the continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.98,0:30:44.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们穿越撒哈拉沙漠时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As they travel across the Sahara
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.22,0:30:47.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,造成了世界上最大的沙尘暴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they create the biggest of all sand storms
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.54,0:30:49.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沙子被吹到地球的另一头\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}blowing sand halfway round the world
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.90,0:30:53.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,亚马逊丛林因此而变得肥沃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to fertilize the Amazon jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.82,0:31:00.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风掠过整个印度洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Winds blowing across the Indian Ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.90,0:31:05.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一边收集水气  一边扑向北方的喜玛拉雅山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}collect moisture and sweep northwards towards the Himalayas.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.62,0:31:10.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着气流的上升 温度也逐渐下降\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the air rises, so it cools.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.02,0:31:17.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,携带的水气开始凝结 汇集成云\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The water it carries condenses into clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.78,0:31:22.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后变成季风雨落到地面  滋润大地万物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and then falls as the life giving rains of the monsoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.42,0:31:30.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至此 由太阳驱动的大气环流\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So air currents powered by the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.74,0:31:34.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将潮湿空气带到了大陆中部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}carry wet air to the middle of continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.94,0:31:55.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有水就没有生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Without water there can be no life,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.06,0:32:00.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 水在陆地上的分配极不平均\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but its distribution over the land is far from even.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.62,0:32:10.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠覆盖了地球表面的1/3\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Deserts cover one third of the land's surface
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.58,0:32:13.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且面积每年都在增大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they're growing bigger every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.50,0:32:27.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是南部非洲的卡拉哈里沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the Kalahari Desert in Southern Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.06,0:32:29.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在是旱季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's the dry season
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.82,0:32:35.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数千头大象开始长途跋涉  不顾一切地寻找水源\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and thousands of elephants have started to travel in desperate search for water.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.26,0:32:50.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有横穿南部非洲的野生动物 都怀有同样的目的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All across Southern Africa animals are journeying for the same reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.70,0:32:56.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非洲水牛也加入了这支浩大的队伍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Buffalo join the great trek.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.26,0:33:02.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如此多的动物出于同一个紧急目的 而进行大规模迁徙 这在地球上其它地方可看不到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nowhere else on Earth are so many animals on the move with the same urgent purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.58,0:33:10.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的目的地是奥卡万戈大沼泽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're all heading for the swamps of the Okavango,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.50,0:33:12.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一片巨大的内陆三角洲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a vast inland delta.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.26,0:33:16.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这时它仍处于旱季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the moment it is dry,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.78,0:33:18.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是水马上就要来了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but water is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.86,0:33:25.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,肆虐的沙尘暴困住了这群迁徙的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The travellers are hampered by dangerous dust storms.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.06,0:33:33.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母象和小像一不小心就会和大部队分开\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Females and calves can easily get separated from the main herd.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.34,0:33:54.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于这对母子而言  避难所就在前方几英里处的林地内\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For this pair sanctuary lies in the patch of woodland a few miles ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.22,0:33:57.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们不能休息 必须尽快到达那里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They can't rest until they reach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.46,0:34:15.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大部队早已安全抵达\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The main herd has already got there safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.90,0:34:24.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后 掉队者终于从尘埃中走了出来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Finally, the stragglers emerge from the dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.22,0:34:34.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,疲惫不堪的小象仍旧看不清路  因为沙子蒙住了它的眼睛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The exhausted calf is still blinded by sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.18,0:34:39.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母象尽可能地去帮它一把\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Its mother does everything possible to help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.34,0:34:55.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 风暴已经消退\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The storm is now subsiding,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.30,0:34:58.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是 并非所有的象都是那么幸运\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but not all the elephants have been so lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.86,0:35:01.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一头小象迷了路\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One youngster has got lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.22,0:35:05.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管又渴又累\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Thirsty and exhausted,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.26,0:35:08.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它仍追随着母亲的脚步\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it follows the tracks of its mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.10,0:35:11.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不幸的是 它走错了方向\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but sadly in the wrong direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.90,0:35:37.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在卡拉哈里旱季的最高峰时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the peak of the dry season in the Kalahari
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.90,0:35:40.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奥卡万戈迎来了水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}water arrives in the Okavango.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.82,0:35:44.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些水来自数千英里外安哥拉高地的降雨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It fell as rain a thousand miles away in the highlands of Angola
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.66,0:35:48.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奔流了将近5个月才到达这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and has taken nearly five months to reach here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.30,0:35:58.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水将燥热土壤中的昆虫驱赶出来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The water drives out insects from the parched ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.54,0:36:00.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们很快便成了可口的点心\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which are snapped up by plovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.38,0:36:06.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着洪水一块儿到来的鲶鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Catfish, travelling with the flood,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.54,0:36:10.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,捡食着那些被鸟类遗漏的溺水者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}collect any drowning creatures the birds have missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.66,0:36:24.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对所有动物来说 这是一场季节性的盛宴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a seasonal feast for animals of all kinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.10,0:36:39.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鸟类是所有宾客中率先到达的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Birds are the first to arrive in any numbers -
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.34,0:36:41.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,肉垂鹤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}wattled cranes,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.46,0:36:44.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着是黑鹳\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}then black storks.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.78,0:36:49.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鸟类之后就是非洲水牛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Behind the birds come buffalo.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.90,0:36:54.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过数周的长途跋涉  它们终于抵达了终点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After weeks of marching their trek is coming to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.42,0:37:15.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,洪水铺盖了奥卡万戈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the water sweeps into the Okavango
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.06,0:37:21.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡拉哈里的广大地区变成了富饶的天堂\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a vast area of the Kalahari is transformed into a fertile paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.50,0:37:30.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上没有其它地方能比这里 更能清楚地证明水对生命的意义\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nowhere on our planet is the life giving power of water so clearly demonstrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.82,0:37:40.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,动物们逐渐进入奥卡万戈的中心地带  这里的路变得纵横交错\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Okavango becomes criss-crossed with trails as animals move into its heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.90,0:37:48.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新来者开辟了新的干道  洪水流淌在这些「动脉」中 不断向外扩展\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The new arrivals open up paths like arteries along which water flows, extending the reach of the flood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.66,0:38:10.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是非洲难得一见的胜景\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is an Africa rarely seen -
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.34,0:38:13.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个和谐繁荣的水世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a lush water world.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.86,0:38:33.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有的动物干脆在这里安家\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some creatures are completely at home here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.94,0:38:35.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是赤列羚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are lechwe -
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.66,0:38:38.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种羚羊的蹄子张得很开\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}antelope with hooves that splay widely,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.46,0:38:41.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使它们能在水里快速奔走\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}enabling them to move its speed through the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.62,0:38:45.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而有些动物却不是很喜欢这种改变\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For others the change is far less welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.14,0:38:55.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狒狒在水里多少有些不安\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Baboons are somewhat apprehensive bathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.14,0:39:32.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水为所有动物都带来了一个丰收的季节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The water brings a season of plenty for all animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.34,0:39:48.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非洲野狗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Hunting dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.34,0:40:11.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们现在已经成了非洲最稀有的哺乳动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are now among the rarest of Africa's mammals,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.22,0:40:14.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 它们仍是 非洲大陆上最有效率的掠食者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but then nonetheless the continent's most efficient predators.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.26,0:40:19.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的秘诀就是——团队协作\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their secret is teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.58,0:40:26.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑斑羚是它们最喜爱的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Impala are their favourite prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.58,0:40:28.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,捕猎行动开始\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They start to hunt
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.94,0:40:30.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狗群四下分散\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the pack splits up.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.86,0:40:36.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过空中镜头  我们能从新的视角观察它们的战术\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An aerial viewpoint gives a new insight into their strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.98,0:40:38.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狗群一旦接近猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the dogs approach their prey
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.90,0:40:43.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,便立刻分散 占领目标四周的各个位置\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they peel off to take up separate positions around their target.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.86,0:40:58.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们似乎打算对黑斑羚形成一个包围圈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They seem to form a cordon around the impala.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.02,0:41:09.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们悄无声息地逼近\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Moving in total silence
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.26,0:41:11.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后各就各位\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they take up their positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.62,0:41:19.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的耳朵能洞悉最轻微的响声\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Those ears can detect the slightest rustle.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.94,0:41:41.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狩猎开始\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The hunt is on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.50,0:41:49.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,3只野狗紧追一只黑班羚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Three dogs close in on one impala.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.54,0:41:58.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没捉到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.70,0:42:07.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,头犬将黑斑羚赶向侧翼的埋伏区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The lead dog drives the impala towards the hidden flankers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.82,0:42:18.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它估计了一下它们逃跑的路线\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Anticipating their line
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.30,0:42:19.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后立刻从边角切入\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the leader cuts the corner
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.06,0:42:23.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从侧翼加入这次总攻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and joins a flanker for the final assault.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.22,0:42:26.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成败在此一举\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's all or nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.70,0:42:28.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一对一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One on one.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.34,0:42:33.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,野狗拥有耐力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The dog has stamina,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.78,0:42:35.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而黑斑羚拥有速度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the impala has speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.38,0:42:52.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跳入湖中是绝望的选择\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Leaping into the lake is an act of desperation -
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.66,0:42:54.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑斑羚可不太会游泳\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}impala can barely swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.42,0:43:01.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,野狗们知道它们的猎物迟早会上岸  否则就会淹死\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The dogs know their prey must come out or drown -
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.70,0:43:04.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 它们只需等待\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}now it's a waiting game.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.06,0:43:14.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狗群中的其它成员正在发出呼唤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The rest of the pack are calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.74,0:43:17.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们已在树丛中捕到了一只猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They've made a kill in the forest
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.86,0:43:21.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是邀请它们加入宴席的信号\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and this is an invitation to join in the meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.98,0:43:27.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只黑斑羚非常走运\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The impala is in luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.10,0:43:40.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种规模的狗群每天都得进行一次捕杀 并且一起分享猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A pack this size kills once a day and everything is shared.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.06,0:43:52.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只黑斑羚只不过被延缓了行刑的日子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And this impala is reprieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.42,0:44:04.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象群正接近漫长旅途的终点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The elephants are nearing the end of their long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.30,0:44:10.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过数周的长途跋涉  它们都已是精疲力尽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After weeks of marching they're desperately tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.14,0:44:20.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母象首领闻到了水的气味\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The matriarch can smell water
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.22,0:44:23.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它鼓励象群再做最后的努力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and encourages the herd to make one last effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.82,0:44:35.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小象疲惫不堪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The youngsters are exhausted
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.42,0:44:37.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过它们的母亲以前也经历过这种旅行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but their mothers have made this journey before
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.82,0:44:40.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们很清楚水就在不远的前方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they know that they're close to water.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.98,0:45:01.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在完成数百英里的行程之后  它们终于抵达了目的地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After many hundreds of miles they've arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.30,0:46:15.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些大象的生活决定于 一年一度的干湿季节交替\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The lives of these elephants are dominated by the annual rhythm of wet and dry,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.22,0:46:18.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是太阳造成的季节循环\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a seasonal cycle created by the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.46,0:46:50.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球的最南端\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the southern end of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.38,0:46:52.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经历了整整4个月的黑暗后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}after four months of total darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.98,0:46:57.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳重新在南极上空升起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the sun once more rises over Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.62,0:47:15.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 帝企鹅们终于不用再挤在一起了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now at last the Emperor penguins abandon their huddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.22,0:47:18.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄企鹅们仍然看护着它们的宝贝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The males are still carrying the precious eggs
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.14,0:47:22.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在整个漫长的南极冬夜  它们一直呵护着自己的蛋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that they've cherished throughout the Antarctic winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.34,0:47:33.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着太阳的回归 蛋也开始孵化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With the returning sun the eggs hatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.42,0:47:37.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其它鸟还没有到来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Other birds have not even arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.22,0:47:41.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而帝企鹅却熬过了一个漫长黑暗的冬天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the Emperors by enduring the long black winter
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.22,0:47:44.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因而它们的宝宝也有了领先的优势\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}have given their chicks a head start.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.58,0:48:01.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 这些小家伙们已经做好准备  急切盼望着享受南极那短暂的夏天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These youngsters are now ready and eager to make the most of the brief Antarctic summer.

